HEADWORD: Sgraffito
<hw>Sgraf*fi"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Paint.)</fld> <def>Scratched; -- said of decorative painting of a
certain style, in which a white overland surface is cut or scratched
through, so as to form the design from a dark ground
underneath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

